Least squares regression is one of many curve fitting methods available to engineers. This method is a simple method of finding the best straight line to fit a given set of data. Other curve fitting methods can be found on the [[MTE204]] course page.


The final result will be of the form:

<math>y = a_{0} + a_{1}x</math>


Although this result can be obtained using matrix manipulation, the end result can be described by the two following equations:


<math>
a_{0} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^{n}y_{i} \sum_{i=1}^{n}x^{2}_{i} - \sum_{i=1}^{n}x_{i}\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_{i}y_{i}}
{n\sum_{i=1}^{n}x^{2}_{i} - (\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_{i})^{2}}
</math>


<math>
a_{1} = \frac{n\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_{i}y_{i} - \sum_{i=1}^{n}y_{i} \sum_{i=1}^{n}x_{i} }
{n\sum_{i=1}^{n}x^{2}_{i} - (\sum_{i=1}^{n}x_{i})^{2}}
</math>
